                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM CHART CONDITIONS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Chart Condtion Study</Run>
                                references the folloiwng ATM Conditions of the Mid-Term Chart. It displays that condition on the Short-Term Charts.
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0" Foreground="#FF8C00">
                                Mid-Term Conditions displayed as Vertical Lines on the Short-Term Chart
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        MID TERM FT - where the FT Turns Up (Lines colored Lime) or FT Turns Dn (Lines colored Red)
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        MID TERM ST - where the ST Turns Up (Lines colored Lime) or ST Turns Dn (Lines colored Red)
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        MID TERM SC - where the Bullish SC Begins (Lines colored Lime) or where the Bearish SC Begins (Lines colored Red)
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM ELLIOTT WAVE</Run>
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Elliott Wave Study</Run>
                                is an automated momentum-based calculator for Elliott Wave counts across all time frames and markets.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Elliott Wave is not a mechanical trading system.  Instead, it is a collection of tools, theories, methods, and techniques.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Elliott Wave study produces Major, Intermediate, and Minor Wave counts.   These counts are represented by the numbers 1 through 5 and A, B, and C.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM FT CHART LINES</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Chart Lines</Run>
                                represent the midterm FT position on the short term chart when the mid-term FT is either overbought or oversold.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                As the midterm FT becomes overbought, a horizontal lime green bar will appear above the short term price bar.  The horizontal bar
                                will remain green as long as the midterm FT is going up.  Once the mid-term FT turns down, the horizontal price bar will turn red.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                As the midterm FT becomes oversold, a horizontal lime red bar will appear below the short term price bar.  The horizontal bar will
                                remain red as long as the midterm FT is going down.  Once the mid-term FT turns up, the horizontal price bar will turn lime.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM INDICATORS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>


                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Indicator package is made up of the following studies:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM 3 Sigma
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TARGETS
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        SCBars
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TREND LINES
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TRADE VELOCITY
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TRIGGER
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>


                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM 3 Sigma</Run>
                                indicator dynamically calculates support and resistance in the direction of the selected time frame’s current trend
                                and is derived from current volatility.  If in a bull market, it produces resistance lines.  In a bear market, it provides support lines.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Target</Run>
                                indicator identifies potential areas where the market will find support or resistance.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                These targets are similar to Fibonacci Lines but are drawn automatically on your chart once a new trend direction is confirmed.
                                The targets will continue to display until a reverse trend has been identified.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Trend Bars</Run>
                                is a data visualization tool which represents whether a security or index is bullish, neutral, or bearish.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Trend Lines</Run>
                                is a linear study that represents the current direction of the trend plus a projection band representing a user-defined standard deviation.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Trade Velocity</Run>
                                estimates the potential profit and loss of an ATM FT Turn.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Trigger</Run>
                                is a multi-purpose study designed as an oscillator that measures a market’s current strength and oscillation cycles.  It is used for market entry and time risk management.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                ATM Trigger has four unique display elements:
                            </Paragraph>
                            <List Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">FT - Fast Trigger.</Run>
                                        A fast oscillating time algo.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ST - Slow Trigger.</Run>
                                        A slow osciallating time algo.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">PRS - Pressure Line.</Run>
                                        An early indicatiion of trend change.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">TAB - Trend Strength Bar.</Run>
                                        Measures the strength of the current trend.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">MA 200</Run>
                                is a simple moving average of the last 200 Price Bars.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM PREDICTION MATRIX</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The Prediction Matrix is a summary of the last 100 prediction results of Your ML Model. The number of correct and incorrect
                                predictions are summarized with count values and broken down by each class. Each row of the Matrix represents the instances
                                in a predicted class, while each column represents the instances in an actual class.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM TURNING POINTS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Turning Points feature displays the FT and ST turning points for the
                                selected security and time frame.  Green dashes represent the closing price
                                necessary to turn up either study up.   Red dashes represent the closing
                                price necessary to turn down either study down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                Charts can display the turning points for:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Current Price Bar
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Next Price Bar
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Historical
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM X ALERTS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The ATM X Alerts package is made up of the following studies:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM 3 SIGMA ALERT
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TARGETS
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        SCBars
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TREND LINES
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TRADE VELOCITY
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ATM TRIGGER
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <!--<Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Add On Alert</Run>
                                is designed to locate opportunities within the current market direction to identify areas where
                                additional positions may be considered. The alert is trend-following and signals opportunities to buy breaks and sell
                                rallies using a risk level that you set.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                ATM Add On Alerts do not indicate perfect opportunities to buy or sell. Each signal must be considered in conjunction with other indicators and time frames.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                An ATM Add On Alert Up is displayed with a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Circle&quot;</Run>
                                below the Price Bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                An ATM Add On Alert Dn is displayed with a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Circle&quot;</Run>
                                above the Price Bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Exhaustion Alert</Run>
                                ATM Exhaustion Alert is designed to locate potential short term contra trend tops and bottoms.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                An ATM Exhaustion Alert Up is displayed with a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Rectangle&quot;</Run>
                                below the Price Bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                An ATM Exhaustion Alert Dn is displayed with a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Rectangle&quot;</Run>
                                above the Price Bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM First Alert</Run>
                                is a contra-trend indicator that anticipates the failure to continue the previous trend by
                                locating entries near the beginning of a potential new direction.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                An up
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Arrow&quot;</Run>
                                represents the FT Up Alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                A down
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;Arrow&quot;</Run>
                                represents the FT Down Alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Pressure Alert</Run>
                                is designed to locate early contra activity once the ATM FT (Fast Trigger) reaches an oversold or overbought.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Pressure Alert Up will appear as the FT becomes oversold and the price bar has a close higher than 61% of the current range, and the current open is below the close. A ATM Pressure Alert Up is
                                displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;P&quot;</Run>
                                positioned below a price bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Pressure Alert Down will appear as the FT becomes overbought and the price bar has a close less than 61% of the current range, and the current open is above the close. A ATM Pressure Alert Down is
                                displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;P&quot;</Run>
                                positioned above a price bar.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM Pullback Alert</Run>
                                is a trend following condition designed to locate substantial setback opportunities within the current trend.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Pullback Alert Up is displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">diamond positioned below a price bar.</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM Pullback Alert Down is displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">diamond positioned above a price bar.</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM 2 Bar Alert</Run>
                                appear when the price closes two bars in the opposite direction of the ATM FT (Fast Trigger) line.  When the ATM FT
                                is going up, one should expect the price to move up to sideways.  During this condition, price closes can alternate from up closes to
                                down closes. Still, the expected behavior is mostly higher closes.  Therefore, when two closes in the opposite direction of the FT appear,
                                one should question whether the price has sufficient momentum to continue higher.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The 2 Bar Alert Up is displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">blue circle, top half-shaded, below the bar.</Run>
                            </Paragraph>
                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The 2 Bar Alert Dn is displayed by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">red circle, bottom half-shaded, above the bar.</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM X Alert</Run>
                                is an aggressive contra-trend indicator that monitors the ending action of the ATM TSB and the ensuing cycle of the ATM FT.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The condition is represented by an
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;x&quot;</Run>
                                positioned below a bar for a buy alert and above the bar for a sell alert.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM FT Alert</Run>
                                represents when the FT line turns up or down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM FT Alert is represented by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;F&quot;</Run>
                                positioned below a bar when the FT turns up and above the bar when the FT turns down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM ST Alert</Run>
                                represents when the ST line turns up or down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM ST Alert is represented by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">S&quot;</Run>
                                positioned below a bar when the ST turns up and above the bar when the ST turns down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                The
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ATM FTST Alert</Run>
                                represents when the FT and ST lines both turn together. It is a price exhaustion condition.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="40,20,0,0">
                                The ATM FTST Alert is represented by a
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">&quot;B&quot;</Run>
                                positioned below a bar when the FT and ST turns up and above the bar when the FT and ST turns down.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">FUNDAMENTALS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,20,0,0">
                                Equity Only feature.  Selecting Fundamentals displays the
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">Next Earnings Date</Run>
                                for the Stock.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph />

